the 31st cannes film festival was held on may 16-30. the palme d'or went to the l'albero degli zoccoli by ermanno olmi. this festival saw the introduction of a new non-competitive section, 'un certain regard', which replaces 'les yeux fertiles' (1975-1977), 'l'air du temps' and 'le passé composé'. the festival opened with moy laskovyy i nezhnyy zver, directed by emil loteanu and closed with fedora, directed by billy wilder.